comments: Finney-Smith (DAL) is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Correctly called 24 Second Violation on CLE.
LeVert (CLE) establishes a legal position outside of the RA, and Finney-Smith (DAL) goes through LeVert when the body contact occurs following the pass.
Mobley (CLE) and Bullock (DAL) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs as the pick is set.

Finney-Smith (DAL) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he moves to imminently guard Allen (CLE). Finney-Smith then moves away from Allen for less than three seconds when the shot is imminent.
Wood (DAL) briefly rests a hand on Mitchell's (CLE) back and marginal contact occurs, prior to the blocked shot by Wood.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the floor of a defensive goaltending by Wood (DAL) is overturned and DAL is given possession of the ball.
Garland (CLE) initiates illegal contact with Wood (DAL) as he attempts to get to the pass.
Mitchell (CLE) makes contact with Wood's (CLE) head/face as he gathers the pass, which affects his SQBR.
Mitchell (CLE) maintains his right foot as his pivot prior to releasing the pass.
Mobley (CLE) is imminently exiting the lane within three seconds.
Finney-Smith (DAL) extends his right arm forward and initiates incidental contact with Mobley's (CLE) left arm after making contact with the ball.
Mitchell (CLE) delivers body contact to Walker (DAL) and affects his SQBR during the drive. Any head contact that occurs to Mitchell is incidental.
Finney-Smith (DAL) commits a take foul on Allen (CLE).
Allen (CLE) brings his arm toward Walker's (DAL) path and marginal contact occurs during the drive.
Hardaway Jr. (DAL) and Garland (CLE) engage and disengage off-ball during the in-bound play.
Mobley (CLE) releases the inbound pass within five seconds.
Allen (CLE) is absorbing the initial contact that occurs with Hardaway Jr. (DAL) and incidental contact occurs as Hardaway Jr. attempts to move over the screen.
Mitchell (CLE) uses his off-arm to clear space from Hardaway Jr. (DAL), which affects Hardaway Jr.'s ability to defend.
Wood (DAL) is absorbing the initial contact that occurs with LeVert (CLE) and incidental contact occurs as LeVert attempts to move over the screen.
Garland (CLE) maintains a legal guarding position and incidental contact occurs as he defends Walker (DAL) during the drive.
Garland (CLE) engages and disengages with Wood (DAL) as he turns to roll and marginal contact occurs during the pick.
LeVert (CLE) comes through Wood's (DAL) left arm in order to make contact with the ball in the post.
Mobley (CLE) and Wood (DAL) engage in marginal arm to arm contact during the rebound.
Hardaway Jr. (DAL) establishes a legal guarding position in Mitchell's (CLE) path and incidental contact occurs as Mitchell slips by during the driving shot attempt.
Bullock (DAL) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away prior to incidental arm contact occurring thereafter with Mitchell (CLE) during his driving shot attempt.
Allen (CLE) is in the lane for less than three seconds prior to the ball being touched by a defender. Allen then recovers and passes the ball in less than three seconds when the shot is imminent.
Garland (CLE) slightly extends his right leg back toward Walker (DAL) during the jump shot attempt but the contact is marginal.
Correctly called 24 Second Violation on CLE.
Garland (CLE) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Ntilikina (DAL) prior to marginal body contact occurring.
Ntilikina (DAL) and Mitchell (CLE) engage in incidental leg to leg contact as they come together in pursuit of the loose ball.
After Mitchell (CLE) secures the loose ball, CLE is granted a timeout prior to the contact by Ntilikina (DAL).
Hardaway Jr. (DAL) is raising his arm into a vertical position and absorbs the marginal contact that occurs with Allen's (CLE) off-arm during the post shot attempt.
Wood (DAL) and Allen (CLE) engage in marginal arm to arm contact during the rebound.
Walker's (DAL) jump shot attempt becomes lodged between the basket ring and the backboard. Play resumes with a jump ball at center circle.
Mobley (CLE) and Ntilikina (DAL) come together in pursuit of the loose ball and marginal contact occurs.
Mobley (CLE) makes contact with Wood's (DAL) left arm prior to release, which affects his jump shot attempt.
Mitchell (CLE) and Walker (DAL) come together in pursuit of the loose ball and marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
